Indeed, the first episode is broken at 26:13 and it also lacks an AVI index (which prevents seeking).  The AVI index is written after encoding completes, so it's pretty obvious this one errored out half way through.  If you look at the file in a hex editor, the second half of it is just NULL bytes.. no data there.

Rest of the torrent is fine, good quality, etc., but you need to get the pilot (part 1) elsewhere.

/Lost Season 1/Lost - S01E02 - Pilot (Part 2).avi has a malware on it... After having it partially downloaded, Avast detected it as a virus, I of course ignored it cuz well, how is it possible to get a virus from .avi right? Anyway I researched and of course it confirmed telling me it's basically a false positive and any virus that could go into an .avi extension is harmless... Well, 10 minutes later, Antimalware Doctor installed itself (which is known as a pretty big virus), and I of course panicked and set Avast to do a boot time scan and I restarted only to find out it's too late, windows wouldn't run, avast wouldn't run... dead.

I then formatted, re-installed windows, and tried downloading this torrent once again cuz I thought maybe there's a chance that a virus from somewhere else just attached itself to the .avi, but nope... file reached 65% downloaded and WHAM!, Avast detected it again, this time I deleted it and the torrent before it started up again.

There are other torrents out there with that episode, I can't vouch for the rest, but Season 1 episode 1 part 2 is a bad file to download. I'll be downloading from someone else from now on.

And plz, no bashing at my comment, I know it sounds ridiculous that my computer got infected by a .avi file but there's really no way I can prove it, I can just make the warning and then "walk away" hoping someone listens.
Oh oops... Season 1, episode 2 part 2.... my bad.
